OL,3,CThe campaigning maverick Labour MP who
OL,4,Cbecame Margaret Thatcher's friend
OL,6,FFrank Field was a rare beast in
OL,7,FWestminster: he was admired by people
OL,8,Ffrom all shades of the political
OL,9,Fspectrum.
OL,11,FA lofty figure who would spend his
OL,12,Flife tackling poverty and urging
OL,13,Fwelfare reform, the former Merseyside
OL,14,FMP will be missed by many.
OL,16,FBrought up in London by Conservative-
OL,17,Fvoting working class parents, he spent
OL,18,Fnearly 40 years as the Labour Member
OL,19,Ffor Birkenhead and helped Prime
OL,20,FMinisters on both sides of the
OL,21,Fpolitical divide.
