OL,3,CThe campaigning maverick Labour MP who
OL,4,Cbecame Margaret Thatcher's friend
OL,6,FFar from toeing the party line, Lord
OL,7,FField was a man who would stand by his
OL,8,Fprinciples -however much out of kilter
OL,9,Fsome may have seen them.
OL,11,FHe did have rare moments on the front
OL,12,Fbenches but the free-thinker was never
OL,13,Fsilenced when sitting further back.
OL,15,FA former councillor, Frank Field was
OL,16,Fdirector of the Child Poverty Action
OL,17,FGroup until he arrived in Wirral after
OL,18,Fwinning his safe Labour seat in the
OL,19,Fsame general election that put
OL,20,FMargaret Thatcher in power.
