OL,3,CThe campaigning maverick Labour MP who
OL,4,Cbecame Margaret Thatcher's friend
OL,6,FSeen as being on the right of the
OL,7,FLabour Party, he was to become friends
OL,8,Fwith the Conservative PM later calling
OL,9,Fher "a hero" - much to the distaste of
OL,10,Fsome of his colleagues to the left.
OL,12,FWhen the Iron Lady was being forced
OL,13,Ffrom office in 1990, he went to
OL,14,FDowning Street to tell her straight
OL,15,Fthat it was time to go. He was certain
OL,16,Fthat others would not be strong enough
OL,17,Fto speak so bluntly.
